contact_name: Publications Office of the European Union
description: The Events name authority list (NAL) or Common Authority Table (CAT) is a controlled vocabulary listing the events that are part of the legal decision making process with their authority code and label(s) in the 24 official languages of the EU (when available). The Events NAL is part of the Core Metadata (CM) used in the exchange between the institutions involved in the legal decision making process and the Publications Office of the EU. The NAL is under governance of the Interinstitutional Metadata Maintenance Committee (IMMC) and maintained by the Publications Office of the EU in its Metadata Registry (MDR)
title: Events Name Authority List
name: event
contact_address: Publications Office of the EU, Core Business Services directorate, Enterprise Architecture, Methods and Formats unit, Formats, Linguistic Informatics and Metadata section
